2
00:00:07,960 --> 00:00:12,807
["Carol of the Bells" playing]

3
00:00:34,280 --> 00:00:35,725
[Phone rings]

4
00:00:40,880 --> 00:00:42,927
[ring]

5
00:00:43,840 --> 00:00:44,682
[sighs]

6
00:00:45,159 --> 00:00:47,287
- [Beep]
- Hello?

7
00:00:47,479 --> 00:00:49,801
Jesus, Dad. What are you doing
calling the house line?

8
00:00:49,960 --> 00:00:51,200
Mom could have picked up.

9
00:00:52,399 --> 00:00:53,844
No, I do not have any news yet.

10
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,490
- ROSIE: Gerald, is that for me?
- No, Mom.

11
00:00:55,640 --> 00:00:57,529
Mom, don't worry about it,
it's for me.

12
00:00:59,479 --> 00:01:01,847
Look, I'm having everybody
come over the house tonight

13
00:01:02,039 --> 00:01:03,121
to celebrate Mom's birthday,
all right?

14
00:01:03,280 --> 00:01:04,884
And then we're gonna discuss it then.

15
00:01:06,719 --> 00:01:08,051
[sighs]

16
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,081
Oh, you got her a birthday gift.

17
00:01:10,239 --> 00:01:11,924
Well, that's a first.
What was it?

18
00:01:13,039 --> 00:01:15,201
Oh, that. No, no, no,
actually she did tell me about that.

19
00:01:15,359 --> 00:01:16,724
Your wedding video.

20
00:01:16,879 --> 00:01:20,088
Yeah, and what, you thought that was
somehow gonna help your cause?

21
00:01:20,640 --> 00:01:23,769
Look, why don't you come by
the restaurant tomorrow and...

22
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:27,210
I'll let you know what
everyone decides tonight.

23
00:01:28,159 --> 00:01:29,525
But, Dad... Yeah. No, I know.

24
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:32,081
But please,
don't get your hopes up, okay?

25
00:01:32,799 --> 00:01:35,848
All right.
I'll see you tomorrow.

26
00:01:36,599 --> 00:01:37,567
[Phone beeps]

27
00:01:37,719 --> 00:01:40,200
And how many times do I have to
tell you, I don't want a party.

28
00:01:40,359 --> 00:01:43,010
Would you please stop fighting this,
you crazy old woman.

29
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:44,849
All right?
It's already done, it's organized.

30
00:01:45,039 --> 00:01:47,485
Everyone is going to be here
except Cyril.

31
00:01:47,879 --> 00:01:49,325
But he'll be home for Christmas,

32
00:01:49,479 --> 00:01:50,447
- right?
- Yes.

33
00:01:50,599 --> 00:01:52,408
I already told you
he's coming in tomorrow.

34
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:54,049
And he's better?

35
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,406
I don't know.
He says he is.

36
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:57,323
So we shall see.

37
00:01:57,479 --> 00:01:59,801
And you're picking him up
at Port Authority, right?

38
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:01,530
Because he will need
someone there for him.

39
00:02:01,719 --> 00:02:03,882
Yes, Mom.
For the 10th time.

40
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:05,405
- I will pick him up.
- All right, all right.

41
00:02:05,599 --> 00:02:07,567
Don't get yourself all worked up.

42
00:02:07,719 --> 00:02:10,450
I'm just double checking.
He is my baby after all.

43
00:02:10,599 --> 00:02:13,365
Look, Mom, I don't want you
to worry about this. All right?

44
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:14,681
I already spoke to all of them

45
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:16,490
and they're all very excited
to get out here.

46
00:02:16,639 --> 00:02:19,086
Don't try to bullshit me, Gerry.
They're my kids.

47
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:21,725
Yeah, well, look, whether they like it
or not, they're coming out.

48
00:02:21,879 --> 00:02:23,802
I told you I don't want you
to make a big deal out of this.

49
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:26,247
Would you just stop
complaining about this?

50
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:28,163
All right? Look.

51
00:02:28,319 --> 00:02:29,730
Dottie's gonna cook
you a nice dinner.

52
00:02:29,879 --> 00:02:31,165
Connie's gonna bake you a cake.

53
00:02:31,319 --> 00:02:34,085
And Quinn said he's gonna come out
this afternoon to take you shopping.

54
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:36,082
So why can't you just enjoy yourself?

55
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:39,129
Okay. Okay, what's really
going on here?

56
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:42,170
Nothing is going on.
It's your 70th birthday.

57
00:02:42,319 --> 00:02:44,890
I just thought you might like
to have all your kids around

58
00:02:45,039 --> 00:02:46,200
to celebrate with you.

59
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:48,723
Enjoy your French toast.

60
00:02:48,879 --> 00:02:50,006
Gerald.

61
00:02:50,719 --> 00:02:51,606
What?

62
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:54,204
What are you not telling me?

63
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:59,487
Look, there's something I just want
to discuss with the whole family and...

64
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:02,085
I thought it would be good
if we're all together

65
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:03,770
so we could all weigh in on it.

66
00:03:03,919 --> 00:03:05,921
And it has to be done
before Christmas.

67
00:03:20,479 --> 00:03:21,969
[engine starts]

68
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:40,966
[Phone rings]

69
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:42,281
QUINN: Did you make
the reservations for tonight?

70
00:03:42,439 --> 00:03:43,406
WOMAN: Mmm.

71
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:44,971
Did we get the same room
at the lodge?

72
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:47,246
Quinn, she's too young for you.

73
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:49,045
What do you care how old she is?

74
00:03:49,199 --> 00:03:52,123
Well, because it kinda makes you
like a creepy old man.

75
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:53,645
You know, I'm not old enough
to be creepy yet.

76
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:55,211
[Chuckles]
Oh, yeah, you are.

77
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:56,884
- Did you get the same room?
- Yes.

78
00:03:57,039 --> 00:03:57,961
- [Phone rings]
- Where's the ring?

79
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,200
It's at my desk.

80
00:04:01,639 --> 00:04:03,085
QF Design.

81
00:04:03,919 --> 00:04:05,001
Yeah. Hold on.

82
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:07,324
It's your brother.

83
00:04:07,759 --> 00:04:10,603
Um, gonna have to say I'm not here.

84
00:04:10,759 --> 00:04:12,682
Yeah, but I'm not gonna lie for you.

85
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:14,205
Take the call.

86
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:16,290
[clears throat]

87
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:19,481
Yo!

88
00:04:19,639 --> 00:04:20,879
GERRY: Hey, Fitzy, where are you?

89
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:23,007
You just called me at the office,

90
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:24,365
and I'm trying to get out of here.

91
00:04:24,639 --> 00:04:27,211
Oh, okay, good. Then you should
be out here soon, right?

92
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:28,930
QUINN:
Change of plan, my man.

93
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:31,930
I'm taking Abbie up to the Adirondacks
for the weekend.

94
00:04:32,399 --> 00:04:34,004
Got some serious plans in place.

95
00:04:34,159 --> 00:04:37,129
You don't think you can
just stop by for an hour?

96
00:04:37,279 --> 00:04:40,045
All right, then we can show all this off
to your latest flame.

97
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:44,045
Hey, Gerry.
This is more than a flame.

98
00:04:44,199 --> 00:04:47,487
Well, even more of a reason
to stop by then, right?

99
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:50,411
All right. I'll see what I can do,
but no promises.

100
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:52,408
Look, you don't have to
promise me shooot, all right.

101
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:53,408
It's not my birthday.

102
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:55,170
Just the woman that brought you
into this world.

103
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:57,170
See what you can do.

104
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:59,125
[sighs]

105
00:05:00,319 --> 00:05:01,161
[Phone slams onto receiver]

106
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:05,603
[sighing, moaning]

107
00:05:05,759 --> 00:05:07,045
[Horn honking]

108
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:08,651
MAN: Oh, no.
Don't stop, don't stop.

109
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:09,846
[woman whispers, indistinct]

110
00:05:10,279 --> 00:05:11,610
[moans]

111
00:05:11,759 --> 00:05:12,886
[Horn honking]

112
00:05:13,079 --> 00:05:15,081
MAN: No, it's not for you. It's not for you.
It's the neighbor.

113
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:16,605
WOMAN: I gotta see.

114
00:05:16,759 --> 00:05:18,524
Oh, you gotta be kidding me.

115
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:21,403
Oh, shooot, it's my brother.

116
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:24,199
- Stay. I'll be right back.
- Okay.

117
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:33,088
What is this, Gerry?

118
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,605
What the hell are you doing here?

119
00:05:34,759 --> 00:05:35,886
What do you mean
what am I doing here?

120
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,769
I got the supplies
for Mom's party tonight.

121
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:39,125
Oh, shooot.

122
00:05:39,279 --> 00:05:40,247
Oh.

123
00:05:40,439 --> 00:05:42,168
Gerry, I can't host
the party tonight.

124
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,930
What do you mean you can't
host the party? Why not?

125
00:05:44,079 --> 00:05:46,081
I'm having all this trouble
with the boys.

126
00:05:46,279 --> 00:05:47,610
They're in trouble up at school,

127
00:05:47,759 --> 00:05:49,204
and they're not even coming home
for Christmas.

128
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:51,567
So, I...
I gotta deal with them.

129
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:53,927
All right. So what does that have
to do with Mom's party?

130
00:05:55,279 --> 00:05:57,088
Okay, um, there's something else.

131
00:05:57,240 --> 00:06:00,084
I... I was waiting
to tell the family, but...

132
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:03,004
Skippy and I split up.
Like, three weeks ago.

133
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:05,367
I know, because Skippy
was in the bar a couple of nights ago

134
00:06:05,519 --> 00:06:07,124
telling me all about it,
crying on my shoulder.

135
00:06:07,279 --> 00:06:10,762
He also told me that you've been
having an affair for six months.

136
00:06:11,279 --> 00:06:12,610
Yes, I...

137
00:06:12,759 --> 00:06:15,968
I've been seeing someone
and, um...

138
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:18,646
You know, Skippy and I
tried to work it out, but it's just...

139
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:19,687
It's not gonna happen.

140
00:06:19,839 --> 00:06:21,968
Who are you having
an affair with?

141
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:25,249
Do you remember, um,
Jimmy Esposito's little brother Johnny?

142
00:06:25,439 --> 00:06:27,761
Johnny Esposito, the gardener's kid?
How old is he?

143
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:31,207
Uh, I don't know. 20s...
maybe 30s.

144
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:34,011
How did you end up hooking up
with Johnny Esposito?

145
00:06:34,199 --> 00:06:37,362
- He cuts my grass.
- He cuts your grass.

146
00:06:38,199 --> 00:06:39,564
That's fantastic.

147
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:41,245
MAN: Hey, Sharon.
How about I just pop out

148
00:06:41,399 --> 00:06:43,322
and drop you at your mom's
on my way to East Hampton?

149
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:45,004
No, you don't have to do that.

150
00:06:45,159 --> 00:06:46,161
MAN: Not a big deal.

151
00:06:46,319 --> 00:06:48,526
I'm just gonna take the train
or I'll call my brother or something.

152
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:49,646
Not the brother that I met?

153
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:52,411
No, that's Gerry. He's an asshole.
I'll call Quinn.

154
00:06:52,959 --> 00:06:55,850
I wouldn't mind just, like, taking you.
I could see the house.

155
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,843
I could meet your mom,
say "Happy birthday."

156
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:00,127
[chuckles] No, that's definitely
not happening.

157
00:07:00,279 --> 00:07:03,283
I haven't brought a boy home
since my junior prom date.

158
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:05,369
- I learned my lesson then.
- Wow, luckily I'm not a boy, honey.

159
00:07:05,519 --> 00:07:06,362
[Chuckles]

160
00:07:06,519 --> 00:07:08,521
Promise you I'll do better
than your junior prom date.

161
00:07:09,519 --> 00:07:10,362
All right.

162
00:07:12,319 --> 00:07:14,209
So...why don't we do that?

163
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:15,440
Do what?

164
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:18,410
I'll drop you off.
Meet some of the brood.

165
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:22,848
No, you're not seriously asking
to come meet my family today.

166
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:26,011
Are you?

167
00:07:27,199 --> 00:07:28,644
Is that such a bad thing?

168
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:30,247
[Stutters]

169
00:07:30,399 --> 00:07:33,290
No, I just... I didn't think
we were, you know...

170
00:07:33,439 --> 00:07:35,886
at the meet-the-family place yet.

171
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:37,689
I mean, I'm having fun
and you're having fun right now...

172
00:07:37,840 --> 00:07:40,365
Yeah, I'm having fun.
I didn't mean to make it so complicated.

173
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:41,800
- Good.
- It's fun, it's good.

174
00:07:41,959 --> 00:07:43,245
- Okay, good.
- Yeah, that's fine.

175
00:07:43,439 --> 00:07:44,965
- Great.
- Call your bro.

176
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,923
Hey, Erin, the house
looks real festive.

177
00:07:48,079 --> 00:07:49,923
Perfect place for a party tonight.

178
00:07:50,319 --> 00:07:51,685
We can't have everybody over here.

179
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:53,284
I have to put the baby down at 7:30.

180
00:07:53,439 --> 00:07:56,922
Mom said that she wanted to celebrate
at one of her girls' houses.

181
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:59,725
Now I've explained to you
why we can't do it at Dot's.

182
00:07:59,879 --> 00:08:01,040
Connie's place is too small,

183
00:08:01,199 --> 00:08:03,406
Sharon's apartment in the city
is obviously not an option.

184
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:04,641
So that leaves you.

185
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:06,245
Well, we can't do it here.

186
00:08:06,399 --> 00:08:08,606
[whispers] And could you keep
your voice down? The baby's sleeping.

187
00:08:08,759 --> 00:08:10,807
[whispers] I don't understand
why no one seems to think

188
00:08:10,959 --> 00:08:13,088
that their mother's birthday
is a big deal.

189
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:15,766
Because she deals with you one way
and the rest of us another way.

190
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:17,365
You're the golden boy,
you can do no wrong.

191
00:08:17,519 --> 00:08:18,805
She treats the rest of us like shooot.

192
00:08:18,959 --> 00:08:20,961
- I hope you know that that is total bullshit.
- Is it?

193
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:22,406
Do you know
she actually suggested

194
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:24,966
that I let her sneak the baby out
one day and get him baptized.

195
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:26,928
Yeah, she told me
and I think it's genius.

196
00:08:27,079 --> 00:08:28,605
We're not baptizing the baby.

197
00:08:28,759 --> 00:08:29,646
Why not?

198
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:31,370
Because Corey's Jewish.

199
00:08:31,519 --> 00:08:33,328
I thought Corey's an atheist.

200
00:08:33,559 --> 00:08:35,369
- He's still Jewish.
- Look,

201
00:08:35,519 --> 00:08:38,841
just let Mom take the kid
up to church and have her do it.

202
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:42,209
You don't need to participate,
Corey doesn't need to know about it,

203
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:44,327
and that way the kid
is not stuck in Limbo

204
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:46,721
in case you two heathens
are wrong.

205
00:08:46,919 --> 00:08:48,683
You're all crazy.

206
00:08:48,879 --> 00:08:51,008
We're crazy? You're telling me
you're an atheist.

207
00:08:51,159 --> 00:08:52,524
How do you explain
the Christmas tree?

208
00:08:52,679 --> 00:08:55,763
We have a kid now. Where else
am I gonna put the presents?

209
00:08:56,799 --> 00:08:58,211
Why don't you
just blow this thing off?

210
00:08:58,360 --> 00:08:59,963
You know what?
That is not a bad idea.

211
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:01,405
Sharon,
it's your mom's birthday.

212
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:02,806
You gotta stop in for a drink
at least.

213
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:05,929
Oh, no. There is no just stopping in
for one drink with my family.

214
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,047
QUINN: Yeah, that's true.

215
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,964
And let's all be made aware
if we go there at all,

216
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:10,167
we're gonna be there all night.

217
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:11,804
So let's not go.

218
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:13,769
The less I have to deal with Gerry,
the better.

219
00:09:13,919 --> 00:09:15,409
What is this beef with Gerry?

220
00:09:15,559 --> 00:09:18,961
I'm just... I'm tired of him pretending
he's the patriarch of our family.

221
00:09:19,159 --> 00:09:20,605
First of all,
he's not my freakin' father.

222
00:09:20,759 --> 00:09:22,489
And second of all,
he's hardly qualified for the job.

223
00:09:22,639 --> 00:09:24,482
He's a grown man
and he still lives at home.

224
00:09:24,639 --> 00:09:27,370
You know with fairness to him,
he's got his reasons for that.

225
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:29,205
Whatever. The point is,

226
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:30,929
if I don't have to go to
Mom's house tonight,

227
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:32,649
I am more than okay with that.

228
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:36,400
I have an idea.
Why don't Sharon and, um...

229
00:09:36,559 --> 00:09:37,721
I'm sorry,
what was your name again?

230
00:09:37,879 --> 00:09:40,690
Francis Xavier,
but my friends call me FX.

231
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:43,240
- Oh, okay. I like that. It's a good name.
- Thank you.

232
00:09:43,399 --> 00:09:45,721
So why don't Sharon and FX

233
00:09:45,879 --> 00:09:48,167
come upstate with us,
get a room at the same hotel.

234
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:49,970
We'll get dinner,
hang out for the weekend,

235
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:51,769
and we'll drive back
Christmas morning.

236
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:55,648
Honey, you know,
it's really not a great idea.

237
00:09:55,799 --> 00:09:56,846
It's not considerate.

238
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:59,001
Sharon doesn't ski.
It's a ski resort.

239
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,042
Neither do I.

240
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:02,167
You don't ski?

241
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:04,527
You know I got an idea.

242
00:10:04,679 --> 00:10:06,364
I'm headed out to East Hampton
this weekend.

243
00:10:07,039 --> 00:10:09,201
You guys want to come with me,
you're more than welcome.

244
00:10:09,639 --> 00:10:12,211
I've never been to the Hamptons.
