tonight for Rosie's birthday.

332
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:43,883
I know she would
love to see you.

333
00:13:44,039 --> 00:13:46,042
Oh, no. I don't think so.

334
00:13:47,440 --> 00:13:50,761
I don't have the strength these days
to leave the house.

335
00:13:50,919 --> 00:13:53,321
But I'll call her,
I'll wish her a happy birthday.

336
00:13:54,039 --> 00:13:55,565
Yeah, she would love
to hear from you.

337
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:58,040
And I'm gonna make sure
that she gets over here on Christmas Day

338
00:13:58,200 --> 00:13:59,725
to at least stop by and say hello.

339
00:13:59,879 --> 00:14:01,609
Oh, I don't know about that.

340
00:14:01,759 --> 00:14:04,285
I got a phone call from your father.

341
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:06,682
Really?

342
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:08,888
- Mm-hmm.
- This guy is unbelievable.

343
00:14:09,360 --> 00:14:10,246
- What did you say?
- I told him

344
00:14:10,399 --> 00:14:11,605
there's not a shot in hell

345
00:14:11,759 --> 00:14:14,240
that she is gonna let him
into that house again.

346
00:14:14,399 --> 00:14:16,163
Especially, at Christmas?

347
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:18,607
I know. I told him the same thing
but he is insisting,

348
00:14:18,759 --> 00:14:21,081
so tonight
we'll see what she decides.

349
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:22,605
What do you think
that she should do?

350
00:14:22,759 --> 00:14:24,443
What do you think
in your heart?

351
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:26,090
- It's Christmas.
- Yeah.

352
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:28,322
If ever there was a time
for some forgiveness...

353
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:29,720
And mercy.

354
00:14:29,879 --> 00:14:30,880
You're not gonna believe this.

355
00:14:31,039 --> 00:14:32,610
I got this card from my sister,

356
00:14:32,759 --> 00:14:34,807
and it just made me think
of this whole situation.

357
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:36,086
Just listen to this.

358
00:14:36,240 --> 00:14:39,801
"Lost friend, lost child,
lost parent, sister, brother,

359
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:41,404
"husband, wife,

360
00:14:41,559 --> 00:14:43,528
"in the season of immortal hope

361
00:14:43,679 --> 00:14:47,126
"and on the birthday
of immortal mercy

362
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:49,721
we will shut out nothing."

363
00:14:50,240 --> 00:14:52,322
Mr. Charles Dickens.

364
00:14:52,480 --> 00:14:53,970
Great sentiment.

365
00:14:54,159 --> 00:14:56,845
But I think you know how my mother
feels about the English, right?

366
00:14:57,039 --> 00:14:58,451
[Both chuckle]

367
00:14:59,159 --> 00:15:00,365
Now go.

368
00:15:00,519 --> 00:15:01,725
Let me know
how it all turns out.

369
00:15:01,919 --> 00:15:03,888
- Will do. Great to see you.
- [kisses]

370
00:15:04,039 --> 00:15:05,326
All right.

371
00:15:07,919 --> 00:15:09,125
GERRY:
Try to have a good holiday.

372
00:15:09,279 --> 00:15:10,360
I'm trying.

373
00:15:14,480 --> 00:15:17,005
[whispers]
Well, look, how is she doing?

374
00:15:17,159 --> 00:15:18,365
[whispers]
She's good, she's good.

375
00:15:18,559 --> 00:15:21,291
I think the holidays get her
a little down sometimes.

376
00:15:22,440 --> 00:15:26,206
You know, I used to come by
and visit all the time but...

377
00:15:26,399 --> 00:15:28,481
I guess I gotta
make more of an effort.

378
00:15:28,639 --> 00:15:30,369
- Yeah, that would mean a lot to her.
- Yeah.

379
00:15:30,519 --> 00:15:31,806
You should definitely visit.

380
00:15:32,799 --> 00:15:34,370
All right, and, um...

381
00:15:34,519 --> 00:15:37,763
What's your deal?
You're here with her all the time or...?

382
00:15:37,919 --> 00:15:39,763
Yeah, yeah. Definitely.

383
00:15:39,919 --> 00:15:43,605
So, so if you come visit,
I'll see you.

384
00:15:43,759 --> 00:15:44,885
All right, great.

385
00:15:45,039 --> 00:15:47,485
- I will definitely do that then.
- All right. Okay.

386
00:15:47,639 --> 00:15:50,290
Uh, Mrs. G, happy holidays.

387
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:52,885
- I love you.
- Love you, too.

388
00:15:53,039 --> 00:15:55,850
I might come by again,
maybe, uh, tomorrow.

389
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:57,161
Just check in on you.

390
00:15:58,159 --> 00:16:00,288
All right,
see you tomorrow.

391
00:16:00,720 --> 00:16:01,926
- All right.
- Okay.

392
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:03,649
- Good to meet you.
- You, too.

393
00:16:08,720 --> 00:16:09,880
- Bye-bye.
- Bye.

394
00:16:14,480 --> 00:16:16,562
Hey, baby.
How did it go?

395
00:16:16,720 --> 00:16:18,370
It didn't.

396
00:16:18,519 --> 00:16:20,283
What happened?

397
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:21,566
I thought it was a done deal.

398
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:23,005
So did I.

399
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:25,280
What did they say?

400
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:26,566
They didn't say shooot.

401
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:29,245
They just don't have any spots
open, that's it.

402
00:16:29,399 --> 00:16:30,730
I don't understand,
I thought your brothers...

403
00:16:30,919 --> 00:16:31,921
