00:33:22,759 --> 00:33:24,761
Sharon, give yourself a break.

743
00:33:26,160 --> 00:33:28,685
You're not the only one in this family
with daddy issues.

744
00:33:35,799 --> 00:33:39,566
[PA announcements, indistinct]

745
00:33:42,279 --> 00:33:43,361
Yo! C!

746
00:33:43,519 --> 00:33:45,284
Hey, Gerry,
what are you doing here?

747
00:33:45,440 --> 00:33:47,407
How you doin'?
Good to see you.

748
00:33:47,559 --> 00:33:49,926
Figured you could use a friendly face
when you got off the bus.

749
00:33:50,079 --> 00:33:51,763
Thanks. Did you drive in?

750
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:53,371
I did. I did, you know.

751
00:33:53,519 --> 00:33:54,931
And since we're in the city,

752
00:33:55,079 --> 00:33:56,923
there's a little something
I wanna show you.

753
00:33:57,160 --> 00:33:58,684
Okay? All right?

754
00:33:58,839 --> 00:33:59,886
GERRY: You're looking good, man.

755
00:34:00,039 --> 00:34:01,451
CYRIL: Yeah, threw in
a couple of pounds.

756
00:34:01,640 --> 00:34:03,961
GERRY: I think it's good for you.
It's good for you.

757
00:34:04,119 --> 00:34:05,086
CYRIL: Thanks.

758
00:34:11,760 --> 00:34:14,842
GERRY: So, you recognize
this building?

759
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:16,331
No. Should I?

760
00:34:17,519 --> 00:34:19,920
Yeah. You know the picture
in the living room of Dad with Grandma

761
00:34:20,079 --> 00:34:23,208
on his First Holy Communion
sitting on a stoop?

762
00:34:23,360 --> 00:34:25,442
- Right there.
- Oh? This is where they used to live.

763
00:34:25,599 --> 00:34:26,806
Yeah. Third floor.

764
00:34:27,039 --> 00:34:28,610
Well, if the stoop could talk
it'd probably tell us

765
00:34:28,760 --> 00:34:30,762
what an asshole Dad was
as a kid.

766
00:34:32,480 --> 00:34:33,561
How do you know
which building it was?

767
00:34:33,719 --> 00:34:36,121
You know, he used to take me
into the city all the time

768
00:34:36,280 --> 00:34:37,121
when I was little.

769
00:34:37,280 --> 00:34:39,088
He wanted to show me
where he grew up,

770
00:34:39,239 --> 00:34:40,081
how he grew up.

771
00:34:40,239 --> 00:34:42,811
Said, "it's important that you know
where the Fitzgeralds are from."

772
00:34:43,960 --> 00:34:45,563
Never did that shooot with me.

773
00:34:45,719 --> 00:34:48,041
Well, why do you think
I'm doing it now?

774
00:34:49,119 --> 00:34:51,009
You know, he didn't call me once
when I was up there.

775
00:34:51,159 --> 00:34:52,126
I don't know why
that surprises you.

776
00:34:52,280 --> 00:34:54,487
I mean, I keep trying to tell you guys
he is who he is.

777
00:34:55,039 --> 00:34:56,451
All right? And he's certainly
not gonna change

778
00:34:56,599 --> 00:34:57,646
now that he's in his 70s.

779
00:34:57,800 --> 00:34:59,961
Once a selfish cocksucker,
always a selfish cocksucker, huh?

780
00:35:00,119 --> 00:35:01,166
Yes. Yeah.

781
00:35:02,320 --> 00:35:04,606
You should know, though,
he wants to come out to the house

782
00:35:04,760 --> 00:35:06,045
tomorrow for Christmas,

783
00:35:06,199 --> 00:35:07,440
have dinner with us.

784
00:35:08,800 --> 00:35:09,960
What do you think?

785
00:35:13,760 --> 00:35:15,807
If he's gonna be there,
I'm not gonna be there.

786
00:35:18,599 --> 00:35:20,409
[doorbell rings]

787
00:35:23,679 --> 00:35:24,840
Mom, what are you doing here?

788
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:27,731
Dottie just called
and she's just busy this morning.

789
00:35:27,880 --> 00:35:30,041
This is so typical of her.
Busy with what?

790
00:35:30,199 --> 00:35:33,043
She didn't say.
She just asked me to cover for her.

791
00:35:33,199 --> 00:35:34,963
She is so irresponsible.

792
00:35:35,119 --> 00:35:39,010
Oh, everyone has their own issues.

793
00:35:39,159 --> 00:35:42,242
Besides,
what's up with you these days?

794
00:35:42,400 --> 00:35:44,721
Doesn't the holidays
put everyone in a shitty mood?

795
00:35:44,880 --> 00:35:47,405
No, it shouldn't.
it should do just the opposite.

796
00:35:47,559 --> 00:35:49,005
Well, it never has for me.

797
00:35:49,159 --> 00:35:50,400
Is it just the holidays

798
00:35:50,559 --> 00:35:52,005
or is there something specific

799
00:35:52,159 --> 00:35:53,570
- got you down in the mouth?
- Mom,

800
00:35:53,719 --> 00:35:55,130
- I'm really not in the mood
- I mean, no...

801
00:35:55,280 --> 00:35:57,248
- to have this talk.
- I look at this beautiful home,

802
00:35:57,400 --> 00:35:59,971
that loving husband,
that gorgeous child,

803
00:36:00,119 --> 00:36:03,885
and I can't imagine what you've got
to be so down in the mouth about.

804
00:36:04,039 --> 00:36:06,963
Yeah? Well, as usual
you don't know half the story.

805
00:36:07,119 --> 00:36:09,009
Well, why don't you
try explaining?

806
00:36:09,159 --> 00:36:11,242
Mom, we don't have
that relationship.

807
00:36:11,400 --> 00:36:13,050
We never did
and we never will.

808
00:36:13,199 --> 00:36:15,168
You don't even want to try?

809
00:36:15,320 --> 00:36:17,846
Consider it the birthday gift
you didn't get me.

810
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:20,764
Guilt trips, they work
with the others but not me.

811
00:36:21,559 --> 00:36:22,766
- Ah.
- Hey, Rosie.

812
00:36:22,920 --> 00:36:25,081
- You pinch-hitting?
- Hi, Corey, yeah.

813
00:36:25,280 --> 00:36:27,123
- Happy belated birthday.
- Thank you.

814
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:29,248
Where are you two off to today?

815
00:36:29,400 --> 00:36:30,367
Well, we're gonna
have some lunch,

816
00:36:30,519 --> 00:36:32,648
see the tree, do the whole
Christmas Eve thing.

817
00:36:32,800 --> 00:36:35,929
Aha. Oh, so even though
we don't believe in God

818
00:36:36,079 --> 00:36:38,128
we're still celebrating
Christmas?

819
00:36:38,280 --> 00:36:40,282
Doesn't mean you ever stop
believing in Santa Claus.

820
00:36:40,440 --> 00:36:41,851
[Rosie chuckles]

821
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:43,001
You know, Rosie,

822
00:36:43,159 --> 00:36:44,161
today would be the perfect day

823
00:36:44,320 --> 00:36:47,164
for you to do that thing
you asked me about.

824
00:36:47,320 --> 00:36:48,445
- Oh, my...
- Rosie.

825
00:36:48,639 --> 00:36:50,960
If you do it,
don't tell anyone.

826
00:36:51,119 --> 00:36:52,246
Especially this one.

827
00:36:52,400 --> 00:36:54,083
It's between you,
Aaron and God.

828
00:36:54,239 --> 00:36:55,525
- Okay?
- To the grave.

829
00:36:55,679 --> 00:36:56,920
- To the grave.
- ERIN: So, Mom...

830
00:36:57,079 --> 00:36:59,481
Aaron's down now
and he'll go back down again

831
00:36:59,639 --> 00:37:01,483
- in two to three hours.
- Right. Okay.

832
00:37:01,639 --> 00:37:06,248
Now, you two just take your time,
have a great day.

833
00:37:06,400 --> 00:37:08,164
Aaron's in good hands with me.

834
00:37:08,320 --> 00:37:09,367
Oh, I know he is.

835
00:37:09,519 --> 00:37:11,090
You did such a great job
with this one.

836
00:37:11,239 --> 00:37:12,844
I had nothing to do
with raising her.

837
00:37:13,039 --> 00:37:14,371
She raised herself.

838
00:37:14,519 --> 00:37:15,646
Bye!

839
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:31,244
Father Mike,
it's Rosemary Fitzgerald.

840
00:37:31,400 --> 00:37:33,447
Hey, Mom! Look who's home.

841
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:37,239
Hey, Mom!

842
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:40,126
Ma!

843
00:37:41,559 --> 00:37:43,210
Huh.

844
00:37:43,400 --> 00:37:45,527
That's weird.
She must have stepped out.

845
00:37:46,000 --> 00:37:47,445
Uh...

846
00:37:47,599 --> 00:37:50,967
Well, look, the idea was for you
to stay in your old room.

847
00:37:51,159 --> 00:37:52,286
So, you cool with that?

848
00:37:52,440 --> 00:37:53,521
Yeah, of course.

849
00:37:53,679 --> 00:37:55,728
And you're allowed to just
be left here on your own

850
00:37:55,880 --> 00:37:57,722
without any supervision?

851
00:37:57,920 --> 00:37:59,001
I suppose.

852
00:37:59,159 --> 00:38:00,650
Yeah?
Well, what do you think?

853
00:38:01,440 --> 00:38:02,851
- I think I'm good.
- Yeah?

854
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:05,650
- I don't need to lock up the booze or...
- No.

855
00:38:06,159 --> 00:38:07,570
I'll be okay.

856
00:38:07,960 --> 00:38:09,199
All right, brother.

857
00:38:09,360 --> 00:38:10,690
Look, I got to get up
to the restaurant,

858
00:38:10,840 --> 00:38:12,967
but it was awesome
to see you.

859
00:38:13,119 --> 00:38:15,202
- All right? You're looking good.
- Yeah.

860
00:38:17,360 --> 00:38:18,646
Hey, Gerry...

861
00:38:20,239 --> 00:38:22,322
Can I borrow a couple of bucks?

862
00:38:22,920 --> 00:38:24,809
Look, there's plenty of food
in the fridge and...

863
00:38:24,960 --> 00:38:27,360
No. I want to do some
Christmas shopping.

864
00:38:29,480 --> 00:38:31,322
Yeah, of course. Sorry.

865
00:38:34,719 --> 00:38:36,324
That should cover it.

866
00:38:36,719 --> 00:38:37,686
Thanks.

867
00:38:37,840 --> 00:38:38,762
Hey. And don't worry
about anybody else.

868
00:38:38,960 --> 00:38:40,371
Just get Mom something good.

869
00:38:40,519 --> 00:38:41,487
All right?

870
00:38:41,639 --> 00:38:43,880
She's gonna be excited
to see you, brother.

871
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:46,239
Welcome home.

872
00:38:47,639 --> 00:38:48,766
[Door closes]

873
00:38:55,079 --> 00:38:56,844
I think I'm good.

874
00:39:15,239 --> 00:39:16,126
[Knocking]

875
00:39:23,199 --> 00:39:25,009
- [whispers] Hey.
- [whispers] Hey. What's going on?

876
00:39:25,159 --> 00:39:26,809
She's asleep.

877
00:39:26,960 --> 00:39:29,440
- shooot. Sorry about that.
- No. It's cool. It's cool.

878
00:39:29,599 --> 00:39:31,443
Come over here.

879
00:39:31,599 --> 00:39:32,965
- How's it going?
- Good. Good.

880
00:39:33,119 --> 00:39:34,530
What are you doing?

881
00:39:34,719 --> 00:39:38,769
Look, I just wanted to come by
and apologize for last night.

882
00:39:38,920 --> 00:39:39,967
I mean I don't know
if that was...

883
00:39:40,119 --> 00:39:41,644
No, you don't have to apologize.

884
00:39:41,800 --> 00:39:44,121
I had a great time.
It was really fun.

885
00:39:44,280 --> 00:39:48,204
Oh, cool. And I brought a little gift
for Mrs. McGowan.

886
00:39:48,400 --> 00:39:49,322
- Oh, you did?
- Yeah.

887
00:39:49,480 --> 00:39:50,925
What a nice boy.

888
00:39:51,079 --> 00:39:53,650
Yeah, well, I figured it'd give me
a good excuse to come by,

889
00:39:53,800 --> 00:39:54,686
see you again today.

890
00:39:54,840 --> 00:39:57,411
Right, oh...
I'll be sure she gets this.

891
00:39:57,559 --> 00:40:01,201
So, um, what do you got
doing for Christmas?

892
00:40:01,480 --> 00:40:04,722
Well, I volunteered
to stay with Nancy through New Year's

893
00:40:04,920 --> 00:40:06,887
so that the other nurse
could go be with her family, so...

894
00:40:07,039 --> 00:40:08,565
Well, what about your family,
though?

895
00:40:08,719 --> 00:40:10,210
You're not going up to Boston or...

896
00:40:10,360 --> 00:40:12,168
I don't really have anybody left.

897
00:40:12,320 --> 00:40:16,530
Um, yeah, after my dad,
it's kinda just me. So...

898
00:40:16,719 --> 00:40:19,610
Well, in that case why don't you
and Mrs. McGowan

899
00:40:19,760 --> 00:40:21,523
come over
to my mom's house tonight?

900
00:40:21,679 --> 00:40:22,920
It's just gonna be a little dinner.

901
00:40:23,079 --> 00:40:24,922
But at least you're not going
to be sitting here alone.

902
00:40:25,079 --> 00:40:27,047
That would be great.
But she can't leave the house.

903
00:40:27,199 --> 00:40:30,123
The doctor just wants her
to kinda stay put. So...

904
00:40:30,320 --> 00:40:32,527
But we're great.
We're gonna order in pizza,

905
00:40:32,679 --> 00:40:35,889
eat our faces off
till she falls asleep at 8:30.

906
00:40:36,039 --> 00:40:37,929
Then I'm gonna have
a glass of wine, maybe two.

907
00:40:38,119 --> 00:40:40,043
I gotta tell you
that just sounds, uh,

908
00:40:40,199 --> 00:40:41,280
a little bit depressing.

909
00:40:41,440 --> 00:40:43,521
- I mean, for Christmas Eve.
- It's not depressing.

910
00:40:43,679 --> 00:40:45,364
If you think it's so depressing,
why don't you come over?

911
00:40:45,519 --> 00:40:46,965
Come over for the wine part.

912
00:40:48,000 --> 00:40:49,603
You know what,
I would love to.

913
00:40:49,800 --> 00:40:52,086
But I actually...
It's Christmas Eve.

914
00:40:52,239 --> 00:40:53,923
And we've got
this thing going on

915
00:40:54,079 --> 00:40:57,606
with my father
and my whole family that...

916
00:40:57,760 --> 00:40:59,603
that's gonna need
to be addressed tonight.

917
00:40:59,760 --> 00:41:01,842
Yeah. So you're gonna
need a drink.

918
00:41:02,000 --> 00:41:04,480
Yes. I probably will.

919
00:41:04,639 --> 00:41:06,641
So, you know what,
maybe when I'm done with them,

920
00:41:06,800 --> 00:41:09,610
- I could come by here.
- Yeah. Okay.

921
00:41:10,199 --> 00:41:12,327
All right. I'll, uh...
I'll throw a pebble at your window

922
00:41:12,480 --> 00:41:13,322
if you're still up.

923
00:41:13,480 --> 00:41:15,800
All right.
Just don't wake up Nancy, please.

924
00:41:28,039 --> 00:41:29,201
GERRY: [sighs]
What do you say, Dad?

925
00:41:29,360 --> 00:41:31,840
Hey. I was hoping to get
a decent burger.

926
00:41:32,000 --> 00:41:33,081
But no such luck.

927
00:41:33,239 --> 00:41:35,367
Yeah. Well, that didn't stop you
from eating it.

928
00:41:35,519 --> 00:41:36,931
That's probably
why this place is empty.

929
00:41:37,079 --> 00:41:39,889
You know my dad would be heartbroken,
he saw the place like this.

930
00:41:40,039 --> 00:41:41,086
Yeah, well, look,
you're more than welcome

931
00:41:41,239 --> 00:41:43,367
to jump behind the grill
any time you want.

932
00:41:43,559 --> 00:41:45,324
[Dad sighs]

933
00:41:46,079 --> 00:41:47,922
Why don't you get some young people
in here, you know?

934
00:41:48,079 --> 00:41:49,490
Bring the kids in.

935
00:41:49,639 --> 00:41:51,768
Hey, maybe your brother, Cyril...

936
00:41:51,920 --> 00:41:55,925
Good idea. Dad,
Cyril just got out of rehab today.

937
00:41:56,079 --> 00:41:58,400
All right? The last thing he needs
in his life is this bar.

938
00:41:59,840 --> 00:42:00,887
Yeah.

939
00:42:01,960 --> 00:42:04,440
That's another regret in my life.

940
00:42:04,599 --> 00:42:05,806
- I don't even know that kid.
- Yeah.

941
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:07,445
Try picking up the phone.

942
00:42:08,800 --> 00:42:10,085
He won't talk to me.

943
00:42:10,239 --> 00:42:11,445
You know what he told me?

944
00:42:12,119 --> 00:42:13,360
That I'm dead in his life.

945
00:42:13,519 --> 00:42:14,601
Can you blame him?

946
00:42:14,800 --> 00:42:16,722
You were a lousy father.

947
00:42:16,880 --> 00:42:19,121
Exaggerated.

948
00:42:19,280 --> 00:42:22,090
I slapped the kids around
a little bit. But...

949
00:42:22,239 --> 00:42:23,969
that's the way it went
in those days.

950
00:42:24,119 --> 00:42:25,326
I'm not talking about that.

951
00:42:26,320 --> 00:42:28,208
You walked out on us.

952
00:42:29,239 --> 00:42:31,766
- I got back when I could.
- Yeah. Which was never.

953
00:42:31,920 --> 00:42:33,648
Look, I don't even
wanna have this conversation.

954
00:42:33,800 --> 00:42:34,960
So, what else you got, Dad?

955
00:42:35,119 --> 00:42:37,487
Ah, I went to see Father Mike.

956
00:42:37,639 --> 00:42:39,210
I had a confession.

957
00:42:39,360 --> 00:42:41,123
You must have been in there
a while.

958
00:42:41,639 --> 00:42:42,925
Hmm.

959
00:42:43,440 --> 00:42:45,043
We had a good talk.

960
00:42:45,199 --> 00:42:47,088
Well, I didn't with Mom.

961
00:42:47,239 --> 00:42:50,686
I spoke to her and she does not
want this to happen at all.

962
00:42:51,400 --> 00:42:53,481
I don't understand that woman.

963
00:42:53,639 --> 00:42:56,961
All I wanna be is with my family
at Christmas.

964
00:42:57,119 --> 00:42:58,280
Is that so unreasonable?

965
00:42:58,440 --> 00:43:00,806
You're just lonely.

966
00:43:00,960 --> 00:43:02,927
All right? This is your first
Christmas on your own.

967
00:43:03,079 --> 00:43:06,050
After the holidays pass,
I'm sure you will be fine.

968
00:43:06,719 --> 00:43:08,085
No, Gerald.

969
00:43:08,239 --> 00:43:09,480
It's, uh...

970
00:43:11,039 --> 00:43:13,088
It's gonna be my last Christmas.

971
00:43:13,559 --> 00:43:14,925
Your last Christmas?

972
00:43:15,079 --> 00:43:17,969
What are you gonna do?
Kill yourself because of the money?

973
00:43:18,119 --> 00:43:20,327
Because of Carol.
I mean, come on, Dad.

974
00:43:20,480 --> 00:43:21,811
Oh, it's not that.

975
00:43:24,840 --> 00:43:26,329
Well, then what--what is it?

976
00:43:28,639 --> 00:43:30,005
I'm dyin'.

977
00:43:31,039 --> 00:43:32,768
Pancreatic cancer.

978
00:43:33,480 --> 00:43:34,969
Very advanced.

979
00:43:36,719 --> 00:43:40,007
I got four or five months, tops.

980
00:43:41,599 --> 00:43:42,646
[Whispers] What?

981
00:43:42,800 --> 00:43:45,007
I'm sorry. I didn't know.

982
00:43:47,320 --> 00:43:48,764
What are the doctors saying?

983
00:43:51,079 --> 00:43:52,650
That I'm dying.

984
00:43:53,880 --> 00:43:55,563
Oh, Jesus Christ.

985
00:43:57,480 --> 00:43:59,481
Who else knows?

986
00:43:59,920 --> 00:44:01,331
Just Erin.

987
00:44:02,039 --> 00:44:05,168
Driving over to see Dorothy,
tell her, then...

988
00:44:05,320 --> 00:44:08,369
I thought it would be better
to tell each of you face to face.

989
00:44:11,639 --> 00:44:14,722
